caption: SO. GOOD. 🌮🌮🌮 I have a feeling the tacos would be delicious no matter what combination of ingredients you decide on. My husband and I are vegetarians and we used to love the itza tacos at District Taco, but ever since they changed the recipe in recent years, I haven't been able to eat it (for some reason, Beyond Meat makes me sick). So we were thrilled to find the spicy organic tofu at Far East Taco Grille.  The tacos are delicious! It's a good thing we don't live closer because we'd be there every day. I was going to take off a star because they did forget my guacamole once, which is upsetting because it's expensive, and my husband had a less than ideal customer service experience once, but overall the food is great, and I wanted to give the food the rating it deserves: 5/5! ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐

The staff is very friendly (zero complaints there!), however ownership has changed the menu far too many times over the past few years - and not for the better. The Banh Mi Craze burrito used to be fantastic, but now it's just awful. As a vegan eater, I'd like to be made aware if a menu item that didn't contain dairy now suddenly has cheese in it (that happened). Then magically it was changed back again a few months later? They used to have a great menu with quality ingredients and each burrito was consistent! Now it's a gamble every time I go. The last three burritos have been very disappointing (LOADS of rice and almost no "filling") and whatever filling is inside is often concentrated in one section, not spread throughout. Is it the definition of insanity that I keep going back praying it will improve? I guess so. Very disappointed because 3 years ago I gave them 5 stars and loads of praise. If you could turn back time and do things exactly how they were 3 years ago I'd be in heaven.

Quantity: There used to be two egg rolls per order. Now one. And the one we received was noticeably less stuffed with food. If you need a break from your standard taco, try Far East Taco Grill. It's Korean and Mexican fusion.
